doc.ContractDescription: INTEGRATING INFERENCE AND COMPLEX EVENT PROCESSING FOR RFID-BASED LOGISTICS MANAGEMENT RFID IS A PROMISING ELECTRONIC IDENTIFICATION TECHNOLOGY THAT ENABLES A REAL-TIME INFORMATION INFRASTRUCTURE TO PROVIDE TIMELY, HIGHVALUE CONTENT TO MONITORING AND TRACKING APPLICATIONS. A PARTICULAR USAGE SCENARIO OF RFID TECHNOLOGY IS IN LOGISTICS MANAGEMENT AND SPECIFICALLY TO TRACK OBJECTS AS THEY ENTER, LEAVE OR MOVE THROUGH THE ENVIRONMENT SUCH AS THE ISS. WE PROPOSE A PROJECT TO DEMONSTRATE THE TECHNICAL FEASIBILITY OF EMPLOYING COMPLEX EVENT PROCESSING TECHNIQUE FOR TRACKING AND INFERRING THE LOCATIONS AND CONTAINMENT INFORMATION OF TAGGED OBJECTS IN ENVIRONMENTS SUCH AS THE ISS. OUR INNOVATION LIES IN THE USE OF COMPLEX EVENT PROCESSING TECHNIQUES TO PROCESS MULTIPLE RFID STREAMS AND THE USE OF INFERENCE METHODS ON THIS RAW, NOISY DATA STREAMS TO DERIVE LOCATION AND CONTAINMENT INFORMATION AND TO ANSWER QUERIES POSED ON THIS DATA. AN IMPORTANT CHALLENGE THAT WE WILL TACKLE IS TO SCALE THE TECHNIQUES TO A LARGE NUMBER OF CONCURRENT RFID READERS AND THEIR STREAM OF READINGS WHILE ALSO HANDLING TENS OR HUNDREDS OF THOUSANDS OF RFID TAGGED OBJECTS. OUR PROPOSED WORK WILL LEVERAGE CORE ALGORITHMS FOR COMPLEX EVENT PROCESSING OF CONCURRENT RFID STREAMS AND FOR INFERRING LOCATION AND CONTAINMENT INFORMATION OF OBJECTS FROM THIS DATA THAT WE HAVE ALREADY DEVELOPED AS PART OF PRIOR RESEARCH; THESE ALGORITHMS HAVE BEEN EVALUATED USING A LABORATORY RFID SETUP AND USING SIMULATIONS. OUR PROPOSED WORK WILL FURTHER ENHANCE THESE ALGORITHMS FOR SPECIFIC USE CASE SCENARIOS FOR SPACE APPLICATIONS AND INCORPORATE THEM INTO A PROTOTYPE THAT IS CAPABLE OF OPERATING OVER TENS OF CONTINUOUS DATA STREAMS EMANATING FROM RFID READERS AND TRACK TENS OR HUNDREDS OF THOUSANDS OF OBJECTS. OUR PROTOTYPE WILL SUPPORT A SIMPLE QUERY LANGUAGE FOR POSING QUERIES AND ALSO PROVIDE A USER INTERFACE FOR POSING SUCH QUERIES AND DISPLAYING RESULTS. OVERALL OUR DEMONSTRATION PROJECT WILL INVOLVE: (I) DESIGN OF A PROTOTYPE THAT INCORPORATES OUR INFERENCE AND COMPLEX EVENT PROCESSING TECHNIQUES, (II) USE OF TEST RFID DATA FROM NASA JSC OR THE ISS TO DEMONSTRATE THE FEASIBILITY AND SCALABILITY OF OUR TECHNIQUES IN A LABORATORY ENVIRONMENT, AND (III) COORDINATION WITH JSC TO CONFIGURE AND OPERATE OUR PROTOTYPE WITHIN THEIR EXPERIMENTAL CEP FACILITY. RELEVANCE AND IMPACT: RFID TECHNOLOGY HAS STRONG RELEVANCE TO SPACE APPLICATIONS. INTELLIGENT RFID INFERENCE AND COMPLEX EVENT PROCESSING CAN AUTOMATE TRACKING AND MONITORING QUERIES ---THE SYSTEM CAN ISSUE WARNINGS AUTOMATICALLY (WITHOUT REQUIRING CONSTANT CLOSE MONITORING BY LOGISTICS MANAGEMENT STAFF), AND TRIGGER PREVENTIVE ACTIONS TO MINIMIZE THE CHANCE OF HAZARDS OR THE IMPACT OF ANOMALIES. SUCH AUTOMATED TRACKING REDUCES THE CHANCES OF MISPLACING OBJECTS, ENABLES MISPLACED ITEMS TO BE FOUND QUICKLY, OR CAN EVEN PROVIDE ALERTS IF A TRACKED OBJECT GOES MISSING AND HAS NOT BEEN "SEEN" FOR A CERTAIN PERIOD OF TIME. BY ENHANCING LOGISTICS MANAGEMENT WITH AUTOMATION AND REAL-TIME OBJECT TRACKING AND ANOMALY DETECTION, THIS PROJECT IS DIRECTLY APPLICABLE TO FURTHERING THE GOALS OF SPACE EXPLORATION. THUS, THE OVERALL IMPACT OF OUR PROPOSED WORK IS TO DEMONSTRATE THE FEASIBILITY AND BENEFITS OF USING INFERENCE AND COMPLEX EVENT PROCESSING FOR RFID BASED LOGISTICS MANAGEMENT IN SPACE APPLICATIONS.

doc.ContractDescription: WE ARE INVESTING A NUMBER OF ASPECTS OF PHASE SEPARATION IN ATTRACTIVE COLLOID-POLYMER MIXTURES, LOOKING AT SPINODAL DECOMPOSITION NEAR THE BINODAL LINE, AS WE APPROACH THE CRITICAL POINT. THESE EQUILIBRIUM PHASE-SEPARATION PROCESSES ARE DIFFICULT TO STUDY ON EARTH, AS THE TWO PHASES ARE ALMOST ALWAYS OF DIFFERENT DENSITIES. THE STABLE MICROGRAVITY ENVIRONMENT OF THE INTERNATIONAL SPACE STATION THEREFORE PROVIDES UNIQUE OPPORTUNITIES TO INVESTIGATE THESE PARTICULAR PROCESSES, PARTICULARLY AS THESE PROCESSES LEAD TO THE CREATION OF CENTIMETER-SCALE STRUCTURES THAT ARE TOO FRAGILE TO MAINTAIN THEIR SHAPE IN THE NORMAL ENVIRONMENT OF EARTH'S GRAVITY. WE ARE EXTENDING A SERIES OF BCAT EXPERIMENTS, A DECADE-LONG EFFORT TO PHOTOGRAPH PHASE SEPARATION; BASED ON PREVIOUS RESULTS, WE ARE EXTENDING THE SCIENCE WITH NEW COLLOIDAL MATERIALS AND IMAGING AND ANALYSIS TECHNIQUES, TO LOOK AT HOW PHASE SEPARATION MAY INFLUENCE OTHER PROCESSES, SUCH AS GELATION AND CRYSTALLIZATION, ON THESE LENGTH- AND TIME-SCALES THAT CANNOT BE ACCESSED EASILY ON EARTH. WE WILL COMPLEMENT THESE MACROSCOPIC OBSERVATIONS WITH HIGH RESOLUTION FLUORESCENCE MICROSCOPY---WHERE SINGLE COLLOIDAL PARTICLES MAY BE VISIBLE. WE CAN THEN LOOK AT THE EARLY EVOLUTION OF THESE MIXTURES FOR THE FIRST SECONDS AND MINUTES, WITH ACCESS TO EXACT STRUCTURAL INFORMATION. BY COMBINING THESE TWO APPROACHES, PHOTOGRAPHY AND MICROSCOPY, WE WILL BE ABLE TO LOOK AT STRUCTURE AND DYNAMICS THROUGH SEVERAL ORDERS OF MAGNITUDE IN SPACE AND TIME.

doc.ContractDescription: ELECTRICALLY DRIVEN FLOWS CAN PROVIDE SIGNIFICANT ENHANCEMENTS TO CURRENT AND FUTURE TECHNOLOGIES THAT CAN BENEFIT FROM INCREASED HEAT TRANSFER AND MASS TRANSPORT CAPACITIES IN MACRO AND MICRO SCALES. IN PARTICULAR, ELECTRICALLY GENERATED FLOWS (WITH AND WITHOUT PHASE CHANGE) HAVE GREAT POTENTIAL FOR TERRESTRIAL AND MICRO-GRAVITY APPLICATIONS. ELECTROHYDRODYNAMIC (EHD) ION-DRAGGING PUMPING AND INDUCTION PUMPING HAVE BEEN EXTENSIVELY STUDIED IN THE PAST SEVERAL DECADES WITH NO SIGNIFICANT, SUCCESSFUL APPLICATIONS. ON THE CONTRARY EDH PUMPING BASED ON CONDUCTION PHENOMENON HAS REACHED A STAGE WHERE VARIOUS APPLICATIONS ARE EXPECTED IN THE NEAR FUTURE, SINCE PRESSURE HEADS ON THE ORDER OF KILO PASCAL PER ELECTRODE PAIR ARE EASILY OBTAINABLE. EHD CONDUCTION PUMPS ARE SIMPLE IN DESIGN, LIGHTWEIGHT NON-MECHANICAL, AND FREE OF VIBRATION AND NOISE AND THEY ALLOW FOR ACTIVE CONTROL OF HEAT TRANSFER AND MASS TRANSPORT. EHD CONDUCTION PUMPING REQUIRES MINIMAL ELECTRIC POWER TO OPERATE (AT LEAST THREE ORDERS OF MAGNITUDE LESS: POWER COMPARED TO THE RESULTANT HEAT TRANSPORT CAPACITY). THIS PROPOSED RESEARCH WILL FUNDAMENTALLY INVESTIGATE THE ELECTRICALLY-DRIVEN DIELECTRIC LIQUID FILM IN THE PRESENCE OF PHASE CHANGE IN MACRO- AND MICRO-SCALES BASED ON CONDUCTION PHENOMENON THROUGH A COMBINED EXPERIMENTAL AND COMPUTATIONAL INVESTIGATION. FURTHERMORE THE COUPLING OF ELECTRIC DOUBLE LAYERS AND HETEROCHARGE LAYERS, IN MICRO-CHANNELS WILL BE EXPLORED, AND THE NON-DIMENSIONAL THRESHOLD AT WHICH THE DOUBLE LAYER STARTS TO AFFECT THE CORRESPONDING FLOW FIELD WIN BE DETERMINED. NOTE THAT IN MICRO-SCALES THE DEBYE LENGTH WITHIN DIELECTRIC FLUIDS BECOMES COMPARABLE TO THE CONDUIT DIMENSIONS. ADDITIONALLY, UNIQUE TWO-PHASE HEAT TRANSPORT DEVICES WILL BE DEVELOPED THAT WILL OPERATE BASED ON THE CONDUCTION PHENOMENON, WITH OR WITHOUT CAPILLARY EFFECTS IN MACRO AND MICRO-SCALES. HEAT FLUX LEVELS WITH THESE ACTIVE MICRO-SCALE HEAT TRANSPORT DEVICES ARE EXPECTED TO SIGNIFICANTLY EXCEED THE CORRESPONDING WORKING FLUID CRITICAL HEAT FLUX LEVEL WHILE OPERATING STABLY AND FOR EXAMPLE REACHING MUCH ABOVE 300 W/CM2 FOR REFRIGERANT R-123.

doc.ContractDescription: IT IS WELL ESTABLISHED THAT SLEEP DEFICIENCY AND CIRCADIAN DESYNCHRONY IMPAIR ALERTNESS AND PERFORMANCE. THIS IS OF CONCERN GIVEN THAT CHRONIC SLEEP LOSS IS HIGHLY PREVALENT DURING SPACE MISSIONS, WHICH ALSO OFTEN REQUIRE MAINTENANCE OF UNUSUAL SLEEP-WAKE AND WORK SCHEDULES THAT THE CIRCADIAN SYSTEM DOES NOT READILY ADAPT TO, FURTHER INCREASING SLEEPINESS AND REDUCING SLEEP. IN SUCH A HIGH-RISK ENVIRONMENT, THE RISK OF SLEEPINESS-RELATED PERFORMANCE IMPAIRMENT MUST BE MINIMIZED. IT IS ALSO INCREASINGLY RECOGNIZED THAT THE RESPONSE TO SLEEP LOSS AND CIRCADIAN DESYNCHRONY IS HIGHLY INDIVIDUALIZED AND BOTH CHALLENGE- AND TASK-DEPENDENT. THIS HIGH DEGREE OF INTER-INDIVIDUAL VARIABILITY MAKES IT VERY DIFFICULT TO PREDICT WHO WILL BE AT RISK AND WHEN THEY WILL BE AT RISK, AND THEREFORE A 'ONE-SIZEFITS-ALL' APPROACH IS LIKELY TO BE SUBOPTIMAL. WHAT IS NEEDED ARE BIOMARKERS OF INDIVIDUAL VULNERABILITIES AND RESILIENCIES TO SLEEP LOSS AND CIRCADIAN DESYNCHRONIZATION THAT CAN BE USED TO PREDICT PROBLEMS AND INTERVENE WHEN NECESSARY. TO DATE, THERE ARE NO BIOMARKERS THAT ARE APPROVED TO DETERMINE INDIVIDUAL ASTRONAUTS' VULNERABILITIES TO SLEEP LOSS AND CIRCADIAN RHYTHM DISRUPTION, ALTHOUGH THERE ARE MANY CANDIDATES TO TEST. IN A RECENT NASA EVIDENCE REVIEW ADDRESSING HRP SLEEP GAP4, WE IDENTIFIED AND EVALUATED APPROXIMATELY 80 POTENTIAL BIOMARKERS OF RESPONSE TO SLEEP LOSS OR CIRCADIAN DESYNCHRONY, RANGING FROM SIMPLE SUBJECTIVE ASSESSMENTS OF ALERTNESS THROUGH TO GENETIC POLYMORPHISMS. WHILE THERE ARE FEW DATA SPECIFICALLY CHARACTERIZING INDIVIDUAL RESPONSES TO SLEEP LOSS AND CIRCADIAN DESYNCHRONY, FORTUNATELY, MANY OF THESE BIOMARKERS HAVE BEEN STUDIED BY OUR RESEARCH GROUP IN DETAILED LABORATORY CONDITIONS OF THOUSANDS OF SUBJECTS OVER TENS OF THOUSANDS OF BED-DAYS IN FEDERALLY-FUNDED STUDIES, BUT HAVE NEVER BEEN EXAMINED WITH RESPECT TO INDIVIDUAL DIFFERENCES. FURTHERMORE, IN A PREVIOUS NASA-SUPPORTED STUDY (ROSES-2008), WE STUDIED 51 ANTARCTIC EXPEDITIONERS OVER 6 MONTHS DURING THE ANTARCTIC WINTER (MARCH TO SEPTEMBER) AT AUSTRALIAN ANTARCTIC STATIONS CASEY, DAVIS AND MAWSON (54% OF THE OVERWINTERING POPULATION). A LARGE NUMBER OF SUBJECTIVE AND OBJECTIVE MEASURES OF STRESS, AFFECT, SAFETY, TEAM INTERACTIONS AND WELL-BEING WERE RECORDED, IN ADDITION TO SUBJECTIVE AND OBJECTIVE MEASURES OF INDIVIDUAL BEHAVIORAL HEALTH OUTCOMES INCLUDING SLEEP, CIRCADIAN RHYTHMS, URINARY CORTISOL AND MELATONIN LEVELS, A RANGE OF NEUROCOGNITIVE PERFORMANCE OUTCOMES AND ALERTNESS. THE LARGE DATASET IS AVAILABLE TO TEST THE PREDICTIVE VALUE OF A RANGE OF BEHAVIORAL, PERFORMANCE, SLEEP AND CIRCADIAN BIOMARKERS ON NEUROCOGNITIVE IMPAIRMENT AND GOING FORWARD, WILL ALLOW OUR RESEARCH TEAM, IN COLLABORATION WITH HRP, TO SELECT ONLY THOSE MEASURES THAT YIELD SIGNIFICANT INFORMATION FOR FUTURE STUDY, AND WILL ALLOW CAPACITY TO ADD NEW MEASURES NOT YET ASSESSED UNDER THESE OPERATIONAL CONDITIONS. BASED ON THIS REVIEW, WE HAVE DEVISED A PROTOCOL TO ASSESS THE SENSITIVITY AND SPECIFICITY OF A CORE SET OF THESE BIOMARKERS TO PREDICT NEUROCOGNITIVE AND PSYCHOLOGICAL RESPONSES TO THE SLEEP DEPRIVATION AND CIRCADIAN MISALIGNMENT INHERENT IN ISS OPERATIONS. FIRST, WE WILL IDENTIFY CANDIDATE BIOMARKERS FROM OUR LABORATORY ANALOG, WHERE INDIVIDUALS ARE HOUSED IN INDIVIDUAL, SEMI-ISOLATED, WINDOW-LESS SUITES, AND FROM EXISTING EXTENSIVE LONGITUDINAL DATA IN OVER 50 ANTARCTIC EXPEDITIONERS. THESE, AND PREVIOUSLY UNTESTED BIOMARKERS, WILL THEN BE VALIDATED IN NEW LIMITED LABORATORY ANALOG STUDIES TO INFORM A NEW ANALOG STUDY THAT WILL TEST THE FEASIBILITY AND UTILITY OF A SET OF CORE BIOMARKERS TO PREDICT AND ASSESS VARIATION IN NEUROCOGNITIVE AND PSYCHOLOGICAL FUNCTION ASSOCIATED WITH LIVING IN ANTARCTICA DURING A 12-MONTH MISSION. THESE INNOVATIVE STUDIES HAVE A HIGH POTENTIAL TO IDENTIFY RELIABLE BIOMARKERS THAT AT SUITABLE FOR OPERATIONAL USE.

doc.ContractDescription: NRI SMALL, A NOVEL POWERED LEG PROSTHESIS SIMULATOR FOR SENSING AND CONTROL DEVELOPMENT ROBOTIC LEG PROSTHESES HAVE RECENTLY BEEN DEVELOPED IN AN EFFORT TO RESTORE NATURAL GAIT IN AMPUTEES. FURTHER RESEARCH IS REQUIRED TO ALLOW THESE DEVICES TO PRODUCE ADAPTIVE AND BIOMIMETIC BEHAVIORS ACROSS DIFFERENT WALKING SPEEDS AND TERRAINS. HERE WE PROPOSE TO BUILD A LEG PROSTHESIS SIMULATOR TO EFFECTIVELY SEARCH THE SPACE OF POTENTIAL CONTROL AND SENSING STRATEGIES TO FIND THE BEST MEANS TO IMPROVE AMPUTEE LOCOMOTION THROUGH WEARABLE ELECTROMECHANICAL TECHNOLOGY. USING A CABLE DRIVE MECHANISM, THE PROPOSED LEG PROSTHESIS SIMULATOR WILL USE OFF BOARD POWER, ACTUATION AND CONTROL HARDWARE TO APPLY TORQUE TO BOTH PROSTHETIC AND RESIDUAL LIMB JOINTS WHILE AN AMPUTEE PARTICIPANT WALKS ON AN INSTRUMENTED TREADMILL. THE APPLIED TORQUE PROFILES WILL BE DETERMINED FROM A NEUROMUSCULAR MODEL BASED CONTROL PARADIGM. THE NEUROMUSCULAR MODEL WILL INCLUDE OPTIMIZED MUSCLE TENDON PARAMETERS AS WELL AS A REFLEXIVE FEEDBACK BASED CONTROL SCHEME FOR EACH MUSCLE. FOR A GIVEN AMPUTEE TEST PARTICIPANT, THE MODEL WILL BE TUNED TO MATCH THE PARAMETERS DERIVED FROM A HEIGHT AND WEIGHT MATCHED PERSON WITHOUT AMPUTATION. THE PROPOSED RESEARCH PROGRAM SHALL INCLUDE TWO PHASES. IN A FIRST PHASE, 2.5 YEARS, WE PROPOSE TO DESIGN AND FABRICATE THE TRANSTIBIAL PROSTHESIS SIMULATOR APPARATUS, PROGRAM THE MODEL BASED CONTROL AND SENSING PARADIGMS, AND CLINICALLY EVALUATE THESE PARADIGMS ON WALKING TRANSTIBIAL AMPUTEES THROUGH BIOMECHANICAL AND PHYSIOLOGICAL MEASURES. IN A SECOND PHASE, 2.5 YEARS, WE PROPOSE TO DESIGN AND FABRICATE THE TRANSFEMORAL PROSTHESIS SIMULATOR APPARATUS, PROGRAM THE MODEL BASED CONTROL AND SENSING PARADIGMS, AND EVALUATE THESE PARADIGMS ON WALKING TRANSFEMORAL AMPUTEES THROUGH BIOMECHANICAL AND HYSIOLOGICAL MEASURES.
